nt_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":3314032,"name":"Eric Huang","username":"erichuang","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/eb8c5e/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-02-20T23:41:40.472Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks, I counted the number of occurrences of “pts” in the JSON dump since “pts” only occurs once per tag.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public int getNumTargets() {
    return countStringOccurrences(NetworkTableInstance.getDefault().getTable(m_name).getEntry("json").getString(""), "pts");
}

private int countStringOccurrences(String str, String substr) {
    int occurrences = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; str.length()-substr.length()+1; i++) {
        if (str.substring(i, i+substr.length()).equals(substr)) {
            occurrences++;
        }
    }
    return occurrences;
}
